03:28.376 --> 03:31.345
[men moaning]

03:48.362 --> 03:51.265
- WOW! RAGE AND J.T. ARE FINALLY
TYING THE KNOT.

03:51.299 --> 03:52.500
- IT'S ABOUT TIME,
WOULDN'T YOU SAY?

03:52.533 --> 03:53.934
- DID THEY GO
TO TORONTO?

03:53.967 --> 03:56.504
- NO. MASSACHUPITER.
IT'S A PLANET.

03:56.537 --> 03:57.938
- UNLIKE PENNSYLVANIA,

03:57.971 --> 03:59.507
IT'S LEGAL FOR GAYS
TO GET MARRIED THERE.

03:59.540 --> 04:00.874
- AHA!

04:00.908 --> 04:01.942
SO, WHERE DO WE BUY
OUR ROCKET SHIP TICKETS

04:01.975 --> 04:03.344
AND ZOOM OFF?

04:03.377 --> 04:04.612
- HUH. I WISH!

04:04.645 --> 04:05.746
- WELL, UNTIL WE CAN,

04:05.779 --> 04:07.381
WE'LL JUST LIVE
VICARIOUSLY

04:07.415 --> 04:09.383
THROUGH OUR
INTREPID SUPERHEROES.

04:09.417 --> 04:11.652
- LET'S HOPE THAT
5,000 READERS--

04:11.685 --> 04:13.053
OH, WHAT THE HELL,
MAKE IT 10--

04:13.086 --> 04:14.888
AGREE WITH YOU.

04:14.922 --> 04:16.357
- I'LL GET THESE
OUT OF YOUR WAY.

04:16.390 --> 04:18.058
- YOU COMING TO
OUR HOUSEWARMING?

04:18.091 --> 04:19.660
- I WOULDN'T MISS IT.

04:19.693 --> 04:22.396
- IT'S GOING TO BE
A BAD-ASS BLOW-OUT.

04:22.430 --> 04:23.497
- WHAT DO YOU SAY
WE START EARLY?

04:23.531 --> 04:26.467
- MM.
- MM-HMM.

04:29.537 --> 04:31.639
[door closes]

04:31.672 --> 04:33.374
HERE HE IS.

04:33.407 --> 04:35.576
- OUR WAYWARD SON.

04:35.609 --> 04:36.577
- COOL COVER.

04:36.610 --> 04:38.045
- WHERE'VE YOU BEEN?

04:38.078 --> 04:39.580
- I THOUGHT YOU WERE GOING
TO BE HOME BY 6:00.

04:39.613 --> 04:41.081
- I WAS PRACTICING WITH
MY DEBATING PARTNER.

04:41.114 --> 04:42.916
- [chuckles] WHENEVER I USED
TO TELL MY PARENTS THAT,

04:42.950 --> 04:44.652
I WAS USUALLY
GETTING STONED.

04:44.685 --> 04:46.787
- WHEN'S THE BIG EVENT?

04:46.820 --> 04:48.055
- UH, TOMORROW AFTERNOON.

04:48.088 --> 04:49.690
IT'S IN FRONT OF
THE WHOLE SCHOOL.

04:49.723 --> 04:50.991
- WHAT'S THE TOPIC?

04:51.024 --> 04:52.092
- CAPITAL PUNISHMENT.

04:52.125 --> 04:53.527
I'M ALL FOR IT.

04:53.561 --> 04:56.530
I SAY FRY
THE MOTHERFUCKERS.

04:56.564 --> 04:58.532
- NOW YOU SEE WHY
WE'RE SO PROUD.

04:58.566 --> 05:00.000
- [laughs]

05:00.033 --> 05:01.702
- NOW, WHAT I'M
ABOUT TO SHOW YOU

05:01.735 --> 05:03.070
MAY FRIGHTEN
SMALL CHILDREN,

05:03.103 --> 05:04.938
SO PARENTS MAY WANT THEM
TO LEAVE THE ROOM.

05:04.972 --> 05:07.107
[chuckles]
SCARY, HUH?

05:07.140 --> 05:10.411
IT'S WHAT I CALL
THE "COMB-OVER"

05:10.444 --> 05:11.879
LIKE WALLY'S HERE.

05:11.912 --> 05:14.548
BUT SEE HOW MUCH HOTTER
WALLY LOOKS

05:14.582 --> 05:16.850
WHEN HE EMBRACES
HIS BALDNESS.

05:16.884 --> 05:19.086
WH--WHY, WALLACE,

05:19.119 --> 05:20.688
IS THAT A HICKEY?

05:20.721 --> 05:23.090
GO FOR IT, TIGER.
[growls, laughs]

05:23.123 --> 05:26.093
ALL RIGHT. THOSE ARE MY
HAIR DOs AND DON'Ts.

05:26.126 --> 05:27.961
NEXT WEEK, HOME WAXING.

05:27.995 --> 05:29.563
AND I'M NOT TALKING
ABOUT THE KITCHEN FLOOR.

05:29.597 --> 05:33.734
OKAY, EVERYBODY,
BE FABULOUS!

05:33.767 --> 05:36.136
- THANKS, QUEER GUY.
THAT'S IT FOR TONIGHT.

05:36.169 --> 05:39.573
HOPEFULLY,
WE'LL BE "HAIR" TOMORROW.

05:39.607 --> 05:42.443
- MAY ALL YOUR NEWS
BE GOOD NEWS.

05:42.476 --> 05:44.445
- AND WE'RE OUT.

05:44.478 --> 05:46.514
- THANK YOU SO MUCH.

05:46.547 --> 05:48.616
- THAT WAS FABULOUS!
- AW.

05:48.649 --> 05:49.717
- SEE? YOU'VE EVEN
GOT ME DOING IT.

05:49.750 --> 05:51.118
- SORRY, DON.

05:51.151 --> 05:52.486
- SORRY? SINCE YOU'VE BEEN
ON THE AIR,

05:52.520 --> 05:53.854
THE RATINGS HAVE
GONE UP TWO POINTS.

05:53.887 --> 05:55.989
NOW EVERYBODY WANTS
THE QUEER PERSPECTIVE.

05:56.023 --> 05:59.126
CHANNEL NINE HAS EVEN HIRED
A TRANNY WEATHER, UH, PERSON.

05:59.159 --> 06:01.762
- WELL, LET'S JUST HOPE
HE-SHE CAN DECIDE

06:01.795 --> 06:03.664
IF IT'S GOING TO BE
RAINY OR FAIR.

06:03.697 --> 06:04.932
- EITHER WAY, YOUR FANS
ARE GOING TO BE

06:04.965 --> 06:06.133
LINED UP AROUND THE BLOCK
TO SEE YOU

06:06.166 --> 06:07.501
TOMORROW AT HOFFMAN'S.

06:07.535 --> 06:09.002
- SO MANY IN NEED,
SO LITTLE TIME.

06:09.036 --> 06:12.640
- AND WAIT TILL
YOU READ YOUR...FAN MAIL.

06:12.673 --> 06:14.875
- FAN MAIL? FOR ME?

06:14.908 --> 06:19.379
- EVEN PEOPLE
WHO HATE FAGS LOVE YOU.

06:21.915 --> 06:24.818
- HERE YOU GO, HON.
- OH.

06:24.852 --> 06:27.054
OH, THANK YOU, CARL,
BUT...

06:27.087 --> 06:31.792
HONESTLY, I DON'T THINK
I COULD KEEP IT DOWN.

06:31.825 --> 06:33.661
- ARE YOU STILL HURTING?
- [whimpers]

06:33.694 --> 06:36.196
- POOR BABY.

06:36.229 --> 06:38.499
DID YOU TAKE WHAT
DR. MACGRATH PRESCRIBED?

06:38.532 --> 06:39.767
- THAT QUACK?

06:39.800 --> 06:40.934
HE OUGHT TO BE
SPLIT AND QUARTERED

06:40.968 --> 06:42.836
AND SERVED WITH
ORANGE SAUCE.

06:42.870 --> 06:46.807
OH, HONEY...

06:46.840 --> 06:48.576
I MEAN, THERE ARE
ALL THESE NEW DISEASES.

06:48.609 --> 06:52.112
YOU KNOW, DAMN DOCTORS
CAN'T KEEP UP WITH IT.

06:52.145 --> 06:53.714
HMM.

06:53.747 --> 06:56.584
WHAT IF IT'S MAD COW
OR THAT BIRD FLU?

06:56.617 --> 06:57.951
COME TO THINK OF IT,

06:57.985 --> 06:59.520
A PIGEON SHIT ON MY SHOULDER
THE OTHER DAY.

06:59.553 --> 07:00.788
I'VE GOT TO REMEMBER
TO TELL THAT

07:00.821 --> 07:02.723
TO THE NEW DOCTOR.
- NEW DOCTOR?

07:02.756 --> 07:05.993
- I'M GETTING
A SECOND OPINION.

07:06.026 --> 07:07.828
ACTUALLY, IT'S MORE
LIKE A FOURTH.

07:07.861 --> 07:09.830
- OKAY, THAT'S IT.

07:12.633 --> 07:14.868
- WHO'RE YOU CALLING?
- THE STATION.

07:14.902 --> 07:17.070
- I'M GOING TO TAKE YOU.
- CARL, PLEASE, NO.

07:17.104 --> 07:19.206
IT'LL JUST MAKE IT WORSE,
ALL RIGHT?

07:19.239 --> 07:21.208
THINKING THAT I'M KEEPING
YOU FROM WORK.

07:21.241 --> 07:23.143
- [sighs]

07:28.148 --> 07:31.218
- YOU GO SOLVE A MURDER OR TWO.

07:31.251 --> 07:32.620
- I WISH
I COULD SOLVE THIS.

07:32.653 --> 07:36.724
- GENTLY, GENTLY.

07:36.757 --> 07:38.959
- LOOK, PROMISE YOU'LL CALL ME

07:38.992 --> 07:40.861
AS SOON AS YOU HEAR
WHAT THE DOCTOR SAYS.

07:40.894 --> 07:42.930
- I PROMISE.

07:46.867 --> 07:47.968
OOH!

07:48.001 --> 07:49.903
[gasps]

07:49.937 --> 07:52.906
IT'S OKAY, HONEY.

07:57.177 --> 07:59.580
- I'LL BE AT HOFFMAN'S
DEPARTMENT STORE

07:59.613 --> 08:01.048
TODAY FROM 1:00 TO 3:00,

08:01.081 --> 08:02.516
SIGNING AUTOGRAPHS,

08:02.550 --> 08:05.986
GIVING TIPS ON HOW
TO BE FABULOUS.

08:06.019 --> 08:09.256
BE SURE TO STOP BY.

08:09.289 --> 08:10.658
OH, TEDDY, I FEEL AS IF

08:10.691 --> 08:12.860
I'VE FINALLY FOUND
MY CALLING,

08:12.893 --> 08:14.528
THAT GOD HAS APPOINTED ME
FROM ABOVE

08:14.562 --> 08:16.630
TO DO HIS WORK BELOW.

08:16.664 --> 08:20.868
- SAINT EMMETT, PATRON SAINT
OF THE FASHION IMPOVERISHED,

08:20.901 --> 08:23.036
THE STYLE DEPRIVED.
- YOU LAUGH,

08:23.070 --> 08:25.773
BUT THERE IS SOMETHING
ALMOST HOLY

08:25.806 --> 08:27.641
ABOUT SAVING THE THOUSANDS
OF WALKING DISASTERS

08:27.675 --> 08:29.910
IN THIS TOWN.

08:29.943 --> 08:32.913
OF WHICH HE IS
DEFINITELY NOT ONE.

08:38.218 --> 08:39.753
BELIEVE THAT GUY?

08:39.787 --> 08:42.623
WALKED RIGHT BY,
DIDN'T EVEN RECOGNIZE ME.

08:42.656 --> 08:44.625
- BUT I RECOGNIZE HIM.

08:44.658 --> 08:47.227
- IS HE SOMEONE?

08:47.260 --> 08:49.563
- OH, HE'S SOMEONE,
ALL RIGHT.

08:53.200 --> 08:54.968
PRIDE 2002.

08:55.002 --> 08:56.303
WE HAD AMAZING SEX.

08:56.336 --> 08:58.105
AT LEAST, I THOUGHT SO.

08:58.138 --> 09:01.642
THEN THE NEXT DAY,
MET HIM AT WOODY'S.

09:01.675 --> 09:04.645
HE TOLD ME ONCE A YEAR
HE FINDS SOME LOSER GUY.

09:04.678 --> 09:07.648
- LIKE YOU,
AND I GIVE HIM A BREAK.

09:07.681 --> 09:10.651
I GIVE HIM--
I GIVE HIM ME.

09:10.684 --> 09:12.786
THE FUCK OF HIS LIFE.

09:12.820 --> 09:14.955
YOU KNOW,
SOMETHING HE CAN REMEMBER.

09:14.988 --> 09:16.824
IT'S LIKE A SOUVENIR.

09:16.857 --> 09:20.227
IT'S MY WAY OF GIVING BACK
TO THE COMMUNITY.

09:20.260 --> 09:22.329
- TEDDY, THAT WAS EONS AGO.

09:22.362 --> 09:23.697
LOOK AT YOU NOW,
THIN, GORGEOUS,

09:23.731 --> 09:25.933
GUYS FALLING ALL OVER YOU.

09:25.966 --> 09:27.200
- IT WAS THE SINGLE MOST
HUMILIATING EXPERIENCE

09:27.234 --> 09:28.201
OF MY LIFE.

09:28.235 --> 09:31.204
EVERYBODY CALLED ME...

09:31.238 --> 09:34.074
"AUNT PITY FUCK."

09:34.107 --> 09:36.343
- WELL, AS PAINFUL AS
IT MAY HAVE BEEN,

09:36.376 --> 09:39.780
YOU JUST HAVE
TO LET IT GO.

09:47.254 --> 09:50.590
- OR GET EVEN.

09:52.760 --> 09:54.695
- I'M NOT GONNA
MAKE HIM NERVOUS.

09:54.728 --> 09:57.998
I'LL SIT IN THE BACK.
HE WON'T EVEN KNOW I'M THERE.

09:58.031 --> 09:59.967
WELL, I-I JUST WANT
TO SEE HIM IN ACTION.

10:00.000 --> 10:02.102
WE'LL STOP BY
THE STORE AFTERWARDS.

10:02.135 --> 10:07.407
I'LL TAKE YOU BOTH
TO DINNER.

10:07.440 --> 10:10.110
LOVE!

10:10.143 --> 10:12.713
OH, GOD.

10:12.746 --> 10:14.848
CALLIE?

10:14.882 --> 10:16.149
IT'S BEN.

10:16.183 --> 10:18.385
- MR. BRUCKNER. I KNOW.
HUNTER'S DAD.

10:18.418 --> 10:20.287
- HEY, I CAME TO WATCH HIM
DEBATE.

10:20.320 --> 10:22.890
WHICH WAY IS
THE AUDITORIUM?

10:22.923 --> 10:25.726
- AS YOU GO IN,
IT'S ON THE RIGHT.

10:25.759 --> 10:26.727
- AH.

10:26.760 --> 10:28.929
[both laugh]

10:28.962 --> 10:31.732
- BUT I DON'T THINK
THERE'S A DEBATE.

10:31.765 --> 10:35.135
THEY'RE--THEY'VE GOT
A CHORUS PRACTICE.

10:35.168 --> 10:37.037
- WELL, YOU SURE?

10:41.041 --> 10:43.677
- IS HUNTER OKAY?

10:43.711 --> 10:47.014
HE HASN'T BEEN IN SCHOOL
ALL WEEK.

10:47.047 --> 10:48.415
- OH, HE'S FINE.

10:48.448 --> 10:53.721
I-I GUESS I MUST'VE
MISUNDERSTOOD HIM.

10:58.926 --> 11:00.961
- THIS PINK STRIPED SHIRT

11:00.994 --> 11:03.230
WILL LOOK FAB
UNDER THIS JACKET.

11:03.263 --> 11:05.766
AND OH, OH, OH.

11:05.799 --> 11:09.169
AND SEE HOW THIS TIE
REALLY MAKES IT POP?

11:09.202 --> 11:11.438
- FRANKLY, I DON'T CARE
WHAT CLOTHES IRWIN WEARS.

11:11.471 --> 11:13.774
HE TOOK YOUR ADVICE FROM THE
OTHER NIGHT AND SHAVED HIS HEAD,

11:13.807 --> 11:16.176
YOU KNOW,
EMBRACED HIS BALDNESS?

11:16.209 --> 11:17.978
NOW I BARELY LET HIM
OUT OF THE BEDROOM.

11:18.011 --> 11:20.313
- I CAN'T TELL YOU

11:20.347 --> 11:21.915
HOW MUCH IT WARMS MY HEART
TO KNOW

11:21.949 --> 11:23.817
I'M KEEPING HETEROS HORNY.

11:23.851 --> 11:25.786
OKAY. ALL RIGHT,
BE BACK IN FIVE.

11:25.819 --> 11:28.055
IT'S TINKLE TIME!
[chuckles]

11:28.088 --> 11:30.057
- YOU ARE A SUPERSTAR!
- OH.

11:30.090 --> 11:32.459
- MWAH. LOOK AT THIS CROWD.
- YEAH.

11:32.492 --> 11:33.794
- SECOND ONLY TO
WHEN THE STONES

11:33.827 --> 11:34.862
PLAYED
THREE RIVERS STADIUM.

11:34.895 --> 11:39.066
both: MWAH, MWAH.

11:39.099 --> 11:40.801
- BRIAN?

11:40.834 --> 11:42.102
I CAN'T TELL YOU
WHAT IT MEANS

11:42.135 --> 11:43.804
THAT YOU'D SHOW
UP TO SUPPORT ME.

11:43.837 --> 11:45.505
- WELL, I NEEDED SOCKS.

11:45.538 --> 11:47.274
- DON'T PAY ANY ATTENTION
TO HIM.

11:47.307 --> 11:48.876
- HE'S AS PROUD OF YOU
AS WE ARE. AREN'T YOU?

11:48.909 --> 11:50.744
- [scoffs]

11:50.778 --> 11:52.079
YEAH, IT'S AN HONOR
TO COUNT AMONG

11:52.112 --> 11:53.346
OUR CLOSE, PERSONAL FRIENDS

11:53.380 --> 11:56.149
TELEVISION'S LATEST
GAY EUNUCH.

11:56.183 --> 11:57.751
- EXCUSE ME?

11:57.785 --> 12:01.488
- YOU KNOW,
AS IN NON-SEXUAL,

12:01.521 --> 12:03.957
NON-THREATENING,

12:03.991 --> 12:06.159
BALL-LESS.

12:06.193 --> 12:09.229
YOU DO HOMAGE TO A LONG
AND ILLUSTRIOUS LINE

12:09.262 --> 12:10.964
OF LOVABLE,
LAUGHABLE CLOWNS

12:10.998 --> 12:12.866
WHO'VE COME
BEFORE YOU.

12:12.900 --> 12:17.170
WHY, JUST LOOK AT
ALL THESE PEOPLE!

12:17.204 --> 12:18.839
- THEY'RE MY FANS.

12:18.872 --> 12:19.973
THEY ADORE ME.

12:20.007 --> 12:23.376
- BECAUSE YOU'RE SO CUTE.

12:23.410 --> 12:25.779
BUT DO YOU THINK
THEY'D STILL ADORE YOU

12:25.813 --> 12:29.917
IF THEY KNEW YOU TOOK IT
UP THE ASS AND LIKED IT?

12:29.950 --> 12:31.919
- LIKE I SAID, BRIAN,

12:31.952 --> 12:33.253
I CAN'T TELL YOU
WHAT IT MEANS

12:33.286 --> 12:36.857
THAT YOU'D SHOW UP
TO SUPPORT ME.

12:36.890 --> 12:40.127
- ANY TIME.

12:40.160 --> 12:41.328
- I JUST LOVE YOU.

12:41.361 --> 12:43.130
YOU'RE SO CUTE!

12:43.163 --> 12:44.464
- THANK YOU. TH-THANK--

12:44.497 --> 12:47.901
- MA'AM. MA'AM,
STEP BACK, PLEASE.

12:50.603 --> 12:52.472
- HE'S BEEN LYING TO US?

12:52.505 --> 12:55.075
- I'M SURE THERE'S A REASON.

12:55.108 --> 12:56.543
I DIDN'T SAY
A GOOD REASON.

12:56.576 --> 12:58.278
- BUT I THOUGHT
HE TRUSTED US,

12:58.311 --> 13:00.280
THAT, YOU KNOW,
HE TOLD US EVERYTHING.

13:00.313 --> 13:02.349
- DID YOU TELL YOUR MOTHER
EVERYTHING WHEN YOU WERE 17?

13:02.382 --> 13:03.884
- I DIDN'T HAVE TO.

13:03.917 --> 13:05.819
THERE WERE HIDDEN MONITORS
IN EVERY ROOM.

13:05.853 --> 13:07.220
SHE HAD A HOMING DEVICE
IMPLANTED

13:07.254 --> 13:09.089
IN MY BRAIN SOON
AFTER BIRTH.

13:09.122 --> 13:11.291
IT'S THE ONLY EXPLANATION
HOW SHE AUTOMATICALLY KNEW.

13:11.324 --> 13:13.026
- HERE HE--
HERE HE COMES.

13:13.060 --> 13:15.428
NOW, LET'S TRY NOT TO LET
OUR EMOTIONS RUN AMOK.

13:15.462 --> 13:17.064
- WELL, THAT'S EASY
FOR YOU TO SAY.

13:17.097 --> 13:20.067
YOU COME FROM A LONG LINE
OF REPRESSED ALCOHOLICS.

13:20.100 --> 13:21.334
- SORRY I'M LATE.

13:21.368 --> 13:22.903
I WAS IN DEBATE CLUB.

13:22.936 --> 13:24.437
THIS WEEK'S TOPIC IS...

13:24.471 --> 13:28.341
- SECRETS AND LIES?

13:28.375 --> 13:31.511
WE KNOW YOU HAVEN'T BEEN
IN SCHOOL ALL WEEK.

13:35.382 --> 13:37.184
[door closes]

13:37.217 --> 13:38.485
- BETTER.

13:41.254 --> 13:42.856
- WOULD YOU JUST LEAVE ME
THE FUCK ALONE?

13:42.890 --> 13:43.991
I TOLD YOU I DON'T WANT TO
TALK ABOUT IT.

13:44.024 --> 13:46.526
- WE HAVE TO TALK ABOUT IT.

